50|$|Aggravated assault, for example, {{is usually}} {{differentiated}} from simple assault by the offender's intent (e.g., to murder or to rape), {{the extent of}} injury to the victim, {{or the use of}} a deadly weapon. An aggravating circumstance is a kind of attendant circumstance and the opposite of an extenuating or <b>mitigating</b> <b>circumstance,</b> which decreases guilt.|$|R
